The paper analyzes the semantic content of messages exchanged during the 15M movement in Spain using data obtained from a microblogging service. It tests theories on collective emotions and social interaction in collective actions, and analyzes the structure and dynamics of the networks constructed from the digital traces of protesters. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
